name: Boeing 737 Max Dutch roll
summary: Multiple aviation authorities, including the FAA, NTSB, and U.S. regulators, are investigating an unusual "Dutch roll" incident involving a Southwest Airlines Boeing 737 Max aircraft. This rare and potentially hazardous maneuver, which involves a combination of side-to-side and up-and-down oscillations, occurred during flight and prompted the grounding of the aircraft for 20 days. The incident highlights the ongoing scrutiny of the Boeing 737 Max model, which has been involved in previous high-profile accidents.
